Key Match Events: The Spurs outscored the Rockets 52-42 in the paint and had a 28-21 advantage at the free-throw line.
The Rockets stormed back to trim the lead to one in the fourth quarter.
Post-Match Reflections: Victor Wembanyama will hope to continue this momentum as the Spurs looked like a completely different team with him firing on all cylinders.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Victor Wembanyama compensated for Thursday's underwhelming opening night performance against the Dallas Mavericks.
Wembanyama had 17 points, nine rebounds and one block against Dallas on 27.8% shooting.
Others: Wembanyama made good use of his seemingly improved size and strength in this game, and something he must continue doing, looking at the free throw attempts he's generation.
